This is a really
interesting part about sugar

00:17:51.350 --> 00:17:57.160
that I didn't know from a science level,
I just knew from an operational level.

00:17:57.160 --> 00:18:00.180
That when I used to make
sorbets and ice creams,

00:18:00.180 --> 00:18:03.700
if I had something that didn't
have a lot of sugar, it was really,

00:18:03.700 --> 00:18:04.201
really icy.

00:18:04.201 --> 00:18:07.408
And if I had something in which I had
mis-measured, and I put too much sugar,

00:18:07.408 --> 00:18:08.340
it was really soupy.

00:18:08.340 --> 00:18:10.480
And I could never really
figure out why, I just

00:18:10.480 --> 00:18:13.670
made sure that I followed the
